HEADWORD: Passacaglio
<hw>Pas`sa*ca*glio</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>pasacalle</ets> a certain tune on the guitar, prop., a
tune played in passing through the streets.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>An old Italian or Spanish dance tune, in slow three-four measure,
with divisions on a ground bass, resembling a chaconne.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

